msgstr ""

#: app/Strings.php:280
msgid "What date format can I use?"
msgstr ""

#: app/Strings.php:281
msgid "When working with date formats in your table, you have various options to choose from. Avoid using a <span class='date-format'><code>comma separator</code></span>, but consider formats such as <br> e.g. <span class='date-format'><code>2005-06-07</code> | <code>2005/06/07</code> | <code>2005 06 07</code> | <code>June 7- 2005</code> | <code>June 7 2005</code> | <code>7th June 2005</code></span>"
msgstr ""

#: app/Strings.php:283
msgid "Which one is better for link support?"
msgstr ""

#: app/Strings.php:285
msgid "For enhanced link functionality, it's advisable to utilize <span class='date-format'><code>Smart Link</code></span> over the <span class='date-format'><code>Pretty Link</code></span>. Smart Link is known for its robust and user-friendly features."
msgstr ""

#: app/Strings.php:287
msgid "Why my table taking too long to load?"
msgstr ""

#: app/Strings.php:289
msgid "If your table is taking too long to load, it may be due to the presence of a substantial amount of data in Google Sheets, along with images and links. If your sheet doesn't contain images or links, consider disabling <span class='date-format'><code>links and Image support</code></span> within the <span class='date-format'><code>Utility</code></span> settings of Table Customization to expedite table loading. Utilizing the cache feature can also improve loading times."
msgstr ""

#: app/Strings.php:291
msgid "How long table data can take to update if Cache is activated?"
msgstr ""

#: app/Strings.php:293
msgid "When the cache feature is active, updates to your table data are not reliant on your browser's cache. Changes made in your sheet may take approximately 15-40 seconds to reflect. To view the latest updates, simply refresh the page after this timeframe."
msgstr ""

#: app/Strings.php:295
msgid "How do I find tutorials about using the plugin?"
msgstr ""

#: app/Strings.php:297
msgid "Please visit our <a target='_blank' href='https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLd6WEu38CQSyY-1rzShSfsHn4ZVmiGNLP'>YouTube playlist</a>, where we post tutorials on how you can use different features of the plugin."
msgstr ""

#: app/Strings.php:299
msgid "How can I create a table from an imported XLSX file in google spreadsheets?"
msgstr ""

#: app/Strings.php:301
msgid "Make sure to import the XLSX file into Google Spreadsheets in the following ways. Create a new blank spreadsheet, then navigate to `<span class='date-format'><code> File > Import > Upload</code></span>` Drag the XLSX files to import. Then share the spreadsheets from 'General Access'. Please visit our <a target='_blank' href='https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLd6WEu38CQSyY-1rzShSfsHn4ZVmiGNLP'>YouTube playlist</a>, where we post tutorials on how you can use XLSX file imported in google spreadsheets."
msgstr ""

